Norrenberger Financial Group has appointed Ibrahim Aliyu Bala as its chairman, Board of Directors.
He joined Norrenberger Financial Group as chairman of the Board following a unanimous vote by the board of directors.
The statement by the company, said Bala is a distinguished titan of industry with decades of experience in management and engineering.
He is the group executive director in charge of business development of the Lagos Deep Offshore Logistics (LADOL) Base.
Also, Bala had served as managing director of IBK Services Limited, and director of Niya Consultancy, Niya Engineering Limited, Mega Co & Integration and SHI-MCI FZE.
According to the Managing Director of the group, Tony Edeh, “Mr Aliyu a seasoned management maven with a solid business acumen.
The company he said, is excited to welcome him to the board.
“We believe his strong experience in building and leading world class businesses will be valuable as we grow as an organization.”
The statement added that the group’s six-person Board of Directors consists of Tony Edeh, managing director and chief executive officer of Norrenberger Financial Group; Andrew Nweke, managing director of Amborg Global Services Limited; Eniola Adedayo, CEO Goomek Integrated Services; Nduka Ikeyi, founding partner of Ikeyi Shittu and Company and Ifeoma Malo, country campaign director, Power-For-All.